    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-07T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 Tung or Wood Oil/241: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-07T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 7, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference your September 6, noon, regarding wood oil. The information which had
                    been requested by the Japanese authorities here was sent to Japanese Consulate
                    General yesterday and we understand it has been forwarded to Tokyo whence a
                    reply is expected in a day or two. Japanese Consul General told me orally
                    yesterday afternoon that favorable action is being taken but he does not know
                    the details. I am sending you by airmail copy of the information supplied to
                    Japanese Consul General here. If anything further is now required at Hankow
                    please ascertain and inform me exactly what is wanted that is not available at
                    Hankow and is required from firms here.</p>
                <p>Sent to Hankow, repeated to Department, Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
